id: pm-3pbs
title: Reduce default verbosity of pm activity/history CLI output and add a compact mode to pm history
description: "Dogfood (2026-05-20) found the human-facing CLI defaults for pm activity (~809 lines for 18 items) and pm history <id> (~241 lines for one item) dump full JSON Patch ops + before/after hashes per entry. pm activity --compact (4 lines/entry) exists but is opt-in, and pm history has no compact mode at all. The MCP/agent path now defaults to compact (pm-8jd3), but the CLI default and a history compact mode remain. Proposal: keep full patches behind --verbose/--patches and make a condensed view the default (or at least add `pm history <id> --compact`). Changing CLI defaults is a contract change touching several specs, so scope/test carefully."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[6]: activity,agent-ux,cli,dogfood,history,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-05-20T20:32:36.067Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-20T22:09:39.022Z"
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: pm history supports a compact projection; default verbosity of activity/history is reduced (or compact is the default) with full patches available behind an explicit flag; existing specs updated; build + 100% coverage green.
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: fixed
expected_result: "pm history and pm activity default to compact, token-efficient output while --full preserves complete JSON Patch audit entries; contracts/completions/docs/tests stay aligned."
actual_result: "Implemented compact history projection, compact-by-default history/activity CLIs, --full escape hatches, activity full MCP/schema parity, semantic gc cleanup, strict dynamic flag rejection, and full regression coverage."
